  "number": "3.1",
  "title": "About Labs",
  "body": " About Labs   How to structure and document project writeups.    About Labs   Scriber Labs documents projects that link directly to repositories. Each project should have a clear README, overview, design notes, and postmortem.    Project Structure  Each project directory should contain:   README.ptx: Repository link and project scope  overview.ptx: High-level explanation of the project  design-notes.ptx: Architectural decisions  postmortem.ptx: Lessons and reflections     Guidelines   Link to the actual repository early and often  Keep scope clear: what is this project about?  Document decisions, not just implementations  Write postmortems regardless of success or failure  Cross-reference to Scribing where relevant     "
